Daniel Sturridge (born 8 February 1990) is an English footballer who plays for Liverpool and the England national team.
Sturridge was born in Kingston upon Thames, Surrey, England. He is the son of a Jamaican father and a Nigerian mother. He is a cousin of former England international footballer John Fashanu.
Sturridge started his career at Crystal Palace, where he was a regular in the youth team. He made his first-team debut in 2008, coming on as a substitute in a 2–0 defeat to Manchester City. He scored his first goal for the club in a 2–1 victory over West Ham United in the League Cup.
In 2009, Sturridge signed for Chelsea on a five-year contract. He made his debut for Chelsea in a 2–0 victory over Stoke City in the League Cup. He scored his first goal for Chelsea in a 2–1 victory over Manchester City in the League Cup.

Merseyside Police are appealing for information following a fatal collision on the M53.
At around 11.30am on Saturday 30 September, a collision occurred between a lorry and a car on the M53 southbound between junctions 1 and 2.
The driver of the car, a 28-year-old man from Liverpool, was pronounced dead at the scene.
The driver of the lorry, a 47-year-old man from the Wirral, was not injured.
The road was closed for around 12 hours while officers carried out enquiries at the scene.
The road has now reopened.
The family of the deceased have been informed and are being supported by specialist officers.
The investigation is ongoing and officers are appealing for anyone who may have witnessed the collision or who may have dashcam footage to contact @MerPolCC, call 101 or contact Crimestoppers anonymously on 0800 555

The name change comes after the rapper’s wife Kim Kardashian revealed that she had filed for divorce from the rapper in February.
The couple share four children together: North, 8, Saint, 5, Chicago, 3, and Psalm, 2.

English: <s>Grant Anderson's 14th minute try, converted by Frazier Climo, put Ayr in front, but, a yellow card for Scotland cap Rory Hughes, released for the game by Warriors, allowed Melrose to make numbers tell and Jason Baggot grabbed an unconverted try.</s>

The 2010/11 Scottish Cup Final was a rugby union match played on 27 May 2011 at Murrayfield Stadium in Edinburgh, Scotland. It was the 125th Scottish Cup Final and the 24th time that the final had been played at Murrayfield. The match was contested by Melrose and Ayr.
Melrose won the match 19–6, with the only try of the match coming from Jason Baggot.
The match was the first Scottish Cup Final to be played at Murrayfield since 2006, when Glasgow Warriors defeated Edinburgh 21–16.
The match was the first Scottish Cup Final to be played at Murrayfield since 2006, when Glasgow Warriors defeated Edinburgh 21–16.
The match was the first Scottish Cup Final to be played at Murrayfield since 2006, when Glasgow Warriors defeated Edinburgh 21–16.

English: <s>Livingston 1 - 0 Rangers: Menga goal downs Gerrard's men</s>
Spanish: <s>Livingston 1 - 0 Rangers: Menga goal downs Gerrard's men</s>
- "Livingston 1 - 0 Rangers: Menga goal downs Gerrard's men" is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.
Livingston F.C. v Rangers F.C. 1–0 (1–0)
The 2007–08 Scottish Premier League season was the 108th season of competitive football in Scotland and the 107th season of the Scottish Premier League, the top tier of Scottish football. The season began on 5 August 2007 and ended on 30 May 2008.
The season was notable for Rangers' failure to win the league title for the first time since 1998, and for the first time since 1989–90.

True West is a 1980 play by Sam Shepard. It was first performed at the Circle in the Square Theatre in New York City on October 23, 1980. The play was directed by Harold Prince and starred John Malkovich and Gary Sinise.
Plot
Two brothers, Austin and Lee, are in a hotel room in Austin's apartment. Austin is a screenwriter who has just finished a script. Lee is a petty thief who has just been released from prison. English: <s>Now in its seventh year, the Global Citizen Festival will see tens of thousands of people flock to Central Park's Great Lawn to not only enjoy acts such as Janet Jackson, Cardi B and Shawn Mendes, but also to raise awareness for the event's true goal of ending extreme poverty by 2030.</s>
Spanish: <s>En su séptimo año, el Festival Global Citizen se celebrará en el Central Park de Nueva York con la presencia de miles de personas para disfrutar de actos como Janet Jackson, Cardi B y Shawn Mendes, pero también para levantar conciencia de su verdadero objetivo, que es acabar con la pobreza extrema en 2030.</s>
The Global Citizen Festival is a free, ticketed concert held annually in New York City's Central Park. The 2012 Ryder Cup was the 39th Ryder Cup, a match play competition between teams from Europe and the United States. It was held at Medinah Country Club in Medinah, Illinois, from September 28 to October 1, 2012.
The United States team, captained by Davis Love III, won the competition for the first time since 1999, defeating the European team, captained by José María Olazábal, 14½–13½.
The United States team was composed of Tiger Woods, Phil Mickelson, Steve Stricker, Matt Kuchar, Webb Simpson, Dustin Johnson, Jason Dufner, Zach Johnson, and rookie Brandt Snedeker. The European team was composed of Luke Donald, Sergio García, Rory McIlroy, Ian Poulter, Justin Rose, Graeme McDowell, Lee Westwood, Paul Lawrie, and rookie Nicolas Colsa

The Ryder Cup is a biennial golf competition between teams from Europe and the United States. The competition is held every two years, with the European team defending the cup. The competition is named after Samuel Ryder, a British businessman and amateur golfer.
The Ryder Cup is the only golf competition to be played over 36 holes, with each match consisting of 12 singles matches and 12 foursomes matches. The competition is played over five days, with the first day consisting of four foursomes matches and the second day consisting of four foursomes matches. The third day consists of four fourball matches and the fourth day consists of four fourball matches.
The Ryder Cup is played at a different golf course each time. The European team has won the competition 14 times, while the United States has won the competition 12 times. The most recent Ryder Cup was held in 2016 at Hazeltine National Golf Club in Minnesota.

The earthquake was centered 100 km (62 mi) south of the city of Yogyakarta, Indonesia, and 100 km (62 mi) south of the city of Surabaya, Indonesia. The earthquake was felt as far away as the Philippines, and as far north as Singapore.
The earthquake was the deadliest natural disaster in Indonesia in 2006, and the deadliest in the country since the 2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami. The earthquake and tsunami killed 5,000 people, and injured 1,000 more.

The charges also include eight counts of violence and destruction of motor vehicles, and one count of destruction of property by means of fire or explosive.
The document also includes a count of providing material support to terrorists, which carries a maximum sentence of life in prison.
The charges were filed in the Southern District of New York, where the case will be heard.

Wayde Sims (born January 1, 1995) is an American football running back for the New Orleans Saints of the National Football League (NFL). He played college football at the University of Oklahoma.
Early years
Edit
Sims attended and played football at Southmoore High School in Moore, Oklahoma. He was a two-star recruit by Rivals.com.
College career
Edit
Sims played college football at the University of Oklahoma. He was a two-year starter for the Sooners. He was a two-time All-Big 12 Conference selection. He was also a two-time All-Big 12 Conference first-team selection. He was a two-time All-Big 12 Conference second-team selection. He was a two-time All-Big 12 Conference third-team selection. He was a two-time All-Big 12 Conference fourth-team selection. He was a two-time All-Big 12 Conference fifth-team selection. He was a two-time All-Big 12 Conference sixth-

"Paddington's Birthday" is the first episode of the 2017 Paddington TV series. It was first broadcast on 1st September 2017.
Plot
Paddington is celebrating his birthday, and he is very excited. He is also very excited about his birthday present, which is a new hat. However, he is disappointed when he finds out that it is a hat for a dog. He decides to give it to his friend, Mr. Gruber, who is a dog.

The 2018 Ryder Cup is the 42nd edition of the Ryder Cup, a biennial golf competition between teams from Europe and the United States. It will be held at Le Golf National in Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines, France, from 28 September to 30 September 2018.
The European team is captained by Thomas Bjørn, while the United States team is captained by Jim Furyk.
The European team is made up of 12 players, with the top eight players in the European Points List qualifying automatically. The remaining four players are selected by the European captain.
The United States team is made up of 12 players, with the top eight players in the United States Points List qualifying automatically. The remaining four players are selected by the United States captain.
The European team is made up of 12 players, with the top eight players in the European Points List qualifying automatically. The remaining four players are selected by the European captain.
